values: Well, last night Liz was supposed to come over and get drunked up with us but didn't. She had a headache all day and decided not to, so maybe next weekend. In any case, Graeme and I got way fucked up (well atleast I did anyway). He had gone out earlier in the day and got crisps and dip, some cognac and ginegr ale for him, and a bottle of Jager for the both of us. Until I had seen the bottle of Jager I had my mind set on Spiced rum and Dr. Pepper. Well! Ok, so I indulged a wee bit too much in the Jager and got way fucked up haha, but I didn't hurl(much to my surprise). I have mastered the art of no hangover! WEEEEEEEEEEEEEE much drunken tom-foolery to ensue next Friday night should Liz choose to accept the challenge.

Yeah. Haven't updated in a while, but usually I have nothing to update with anyway, so it's of no consequence.

About 3 months ago the cleaning ladies and janies across Scotland went on strike for something that all people, or women as it may be, should have been involved in, but only the janies and cleaners, and canteen ladies were involved in. It was about equal pay, apparently. About a month after the strike, the rest of the carers got letters saying we were getting some money regarding this, based on hours and time of employment with the council. For 6 months employment with the council, I got a decent amount. I did a little shopping, and I'm also getting an ye examination and new glasses. The rest will be saved for sustainment during the summer since I won't be working then. In anycase, this money was a total surprise to me, so I was happy about it, to say the least =D Today I'm expecting my clothes, and sometime this coming wek I should have some new shoes, then Thur I go for my eyes. I can't wait for my new glasses.

Anyway, guess that's all for now.Hope everyone is happy, safe, and healthy.

I feel like I am surrounded,
abandoned, shut out, closed in. 
There's no way out of this.

Blackness is all I can see.
Emptiness - nothingness.
Is anyone out there ?

I cry but no one hears.
I move but no one sees.
I touch, but no one feels.

Did I make this hell for myself?

I cry but no one hears...
my voice just echos.
I move but no one sees...
my shadow just shifts.
I touch but no one feels...my finger tips just go numb.

My head is pounding.
My heart is aching.
I am longing for some company;
longing to be held,
longing to be loved.
Aching to be acknowledged.
Am i still alive?

Did I make this hell for myself?
